subSubSection.paragraph:
Spicules. Megascleres
(
Fig. 11D
). Styles, thick, curved midway, distally hastate or fusiform, occasionally mucronate: 125 (106–143) × 5 (5) µm n=10. Subtylostyles (
Fig. 11E
), straight, thin, distally fusiform with smooth subtylote bases: 127 (85–144) × 1 (1) µm. Acanthostyles, 43 (37–54) × 4 (4) µm (
Fig. 11F
); fusiform, aspinous to finely spinous on base and tip of shaft; midsection finely spinous, spines small and blunt. Auxillary Acanthostyles, slightly subtylote, 52 (46–62) × 2 (2) µm, fusiform, spined from base to tip, spines granular. 
Microscleres
(
Fig. 11G
). Toxas in 2 size categories: I) Long accolada toxas, with sharply angular central curvature and straight arms, 183 (157–192) × 1 (1) µm. II) Short accolada toxas, with sharply angular central curvature and straight arms, 92 (81–109) × 1 (1) µm. Palmate isochelae (
Fig. 11H
) small, unmodified, numerous.
